    "sections": [
      "<p class=\"c5 c17 title\"><a name=\"h.azk7oos3s8cn\"></a><span>Comparing adaption project datasets</span></p><p class=\"c5\"><span>This map or, more precisely, this interactive tool allows to compare the information contained in various collection of adaptation projects financed by public or private funding. Given the high dishomogeneity of such databases, we have only conserved two dimensions of comparison: the countries in which these projects take place and the sectors that they concern. While comparing the databases, keep in mind that they span over different periods and have very different size.</span></p><h1 class=\"c5 c10\"><a name=\"h.undpthsa1rf9\"></a><span>How to use the map/tool and read its results</span></h1><p class=\"c5\"><span>The tool produces a table whose columns of corresponds to the 7 databases offered for comparison and and whose rows can be switched to represent either the countries where the adaptation projects take place or the sectors that they concern. The cells of the table can be switched to show either the number of projects or the total amount of dollars (for the database that contains this information). To allow the comparison across datasets of different size, the absolute values are presented with the proportion relative to the total number of records or to the total amount of funding in each database.</span></p><p class=\"c5\"><span>In order to facilitate the comparison, the relative values of the cells of the table are visualized both as numbers and as repetition of glyphs each of which represents </span><span>1% of projects in the database or 1% of the total funding of the database</span><sup><a href=\"#cmnt1\" name=\"cmnt_ref1\">[a]</a></sup><span>.</span></p><h1 class=\"c5 c10\"><a name=\"h.nfjvr2a5zplw\"></a><span>How the map is built (map building protocol)</span></h1><p class=\"c5\"><span>The tools allow comparison of 7 different databases</span></p><a href=\"#\" name=\"49fea4abf0c60fecfb9fcb69c8a1add79df717c4\"></a>